Make the document adversarial by design. For each headline conclusion, add a one-sentence disproof test:

- A-centered-on-Binance claim fails if pool tick explains centers equally well.
- Drift-trigger claim fails if threshold crossings produce many unacted signals.
- Shoulder/inventory claim fails if B-side is not predictable out of sample.
- Multi-market bot claim fails if other pool interactions are not same contract/call-pattern family.
- Tradable-alpha claim fails if conditional execution improvement is not positive after gas, latency, and slippage.

