We call \(B\) a one-sided secondary overlay rather than a shoulder unless an edge-proximity reporting convention is satisfied. Define
\[
  z_B=\frac{c_B-c_A}{w_A/2}, \qquad \rho=\frac{w_B}{w_A},
\]
and
\[
  d_{\mathrm{edge}}=\min(|i^B_\ell-c_A|,\ |i^B_u-c_A|).
\]
For reporting, the overlay is described as shoulder-like only when
\[
  d_{\mathrm{edge}}\leq \max(120,0.05w_B)
\]
ticks. Otherwise it is reported simply as a secondary band. In this window, the median and range of \(d_{\mathrm{edge}}\) should be reported directly before applying this label.
```

